#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:328
msgid "Animating Palettes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:329
msgid ""
"For Toonz raster and vector levels, colors in a palette can be animated "
"and changed according to the frames of the animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:331
msgid ""
"The animation is defined by keys that refer to timing of the xsheet: this"
" means that there is no relation between the level length and the length "
"of the animation of the palette colors. For example you can create a "
"palette animated from frame 1 to 100 even if its level is only five "
"frames long."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:333
msgid ""
"The color animation will always refer to the xsheet timing, even if you "
"move the related level to a different frame range. For example if you "
"animate a palette from frame 1 to frame 20, and the level is exposed "
"after frame 20, no color animation will be visible and the color used for"
" the level will refer to the last key of the colors animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:335
msgid ""
"Keys are set for all the palette colors and settings (in the case of "
"Special Styles and Textures) at once and can be navigated directly in the"
" palette (with the expected update of the viewer content) to check the "
"color animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:337
msgid "**To define a palette key:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:339
msgid "Select in the xsheet the frame where you want to define the key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:341
msgid ""
"Click the key button ( |Toonz71_140| ) in the top bar of the palette "
"editor."
msgstr ""

