msgid "Navigate the palette keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:359
msgid ""
"Click the key button ( |Toonz71_144| ) in the top bar of the palette "
"editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:365
msgid "Editing Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:367
msgid ""
"Palette styles can be modified with the Style Editor. There are four "
"types of styles to choose from: Color, Texture, Vector and Raster. "
"Generated, Trail and Vector Brushes are available for vector animation "
"levels only. For several types of styles, there is also control over "
"various Settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:369
msgid ""
"An Auto button lets you decide whether the edits have to be assigned "
"automatically to the style, or only after you click on the Apply button. "
"In the bottom right corner you can see swatches for the previous and new "
"style status; if you want to go back to the previous style, simply click "
"on it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:371
msgid ""
"Only the first style in the palette, labeled Color 0, cannot be edited: "
"instead, it allows you to remove any style from lines and filled areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:373
msgid "**To open the style editor as a floating window:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:377
msgid "Choose Windows > Style Editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:379
msgid "Double-click the style you want to edit in the palette editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:381
msgid "**To automatically apply the editing to the style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:383
msgid "Activate the Auto button in the style editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:385
msgid "**To apply manually the editing to the style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:387
msgid "Deactivate the Auto button in the style editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:389
msgid ""
"Click the Apply button every time you want to apply the editing to the "
"style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:391
msgid "**To return to the old style cancelling the editing:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:393
msgid ""
"Click the style swatch in the very bottom right corner of the style "
"editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:399
msgid "Colors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:401
msgid "|style_editor_color|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:403
msgid ""
"Colors can be defined either by Hue, Saturation and Value or by Red, "
"Green and Blue values. They can be used for both drawing lines and "
"filling areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:405
msgid ""
"You can also set the color opacity with the Alpha slider: the lower the "
"value, the more transparent the color. You can check the opacity of the "
"color with the checkerboard pattern visible beneath the color, whose "
"visibility is proportional to the color transparency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:407
msgid ""
"To edit a color you can use either the sliders or the color wheel. To "
"pick a color from the sliders or from the wheel, click it; to adjust "
"values you can use the arrowhead buttons available at each slider ends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:409
msgid ""
"Colors can also be picked from the viewer content by using the RGB Picker"
" tool ( |Toonz71_146| ), whose Type option lets you choose the following:"
" Normal, to pick values of a color; Rectangular, to pick the average "
"values of the colors included in the box you define; Freehand, to pick "
"the average values of the colors included in the area you outline by "
"clicking and dragging; and Polyline, to pick the average values of the "
"colors included in the area you outline by defining a series of lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:411
msgid ""
"If the current style is a special one, the color you edit is the color "
"used by the special style. If the special style uses more than one color,"
" you can select the color to edit in the row of thumbnails available "
"below the Auto and Apply buttons. (see  :ref:`Special Styles "
"<special_styles>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:413
msgid "**To pick the color from the viewer content:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:415
msgid "Select the RGB Picker tool ()."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:419
msgid "Click in the viewer to pick the needed color values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:421
msgid ""
"Set the type to Rectangular, then click and drag in the viewer to define "
"a box which picks the average values of the colors included in the box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:423
msgid ""
"Set the type to Freehand, then click and drag in the viewer to outline an"
" area which picks the average values of the colors included in the area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:425
msgid ""
"Set the type to Polyline, then click in the viewer to outline an area by "
"defining a series of lines and this will pick the average values of the "
"colors included in the area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:431
msgid "Textures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:433
msgid "|style_editor_texture|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:435
msgid ""
"Textures can be used both for drawing lines and filling areas. They can "
"be selected from a list available in the Texture page, where your own "
"textures can be added as well, or added as Custom Texture clicking the "
"Custom Texture button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:437
msgid ""
"Vector texture mapping, that is the way the texture is applied to "
"vectors, is performed using vector parametric coordinates: this means "
"that the texture “follows” the vector’s shape and thickness."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:439
msgid ""
"Custom Textures can be loaded both on PLI and TLV levels, but their "
"parameters can be used only on TLV levels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:441
msgid ""
"Lines and areas texture mapping, applied for raster drawing, use the "
"standard mapping: this means that the texture image is tiled to cover the"
" lines or areas painted with the style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:443
msgid ""
"A more powerful texture mapping can be performed by using the Texture and"
" Pinned Texture special FX (see  :ref:`Toonz Level <toonz_level>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:445
msgid "**To add a new Texture:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:447
msgid ""
"Create the image you want to use as a texture with the following "
"characteristics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:449
msgid ""
"The number of pixels of the width and height of the image has to be equal"
" to 2 to the power of any number (i.e. 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256, "
"etc.); if not, texture images will show stretched."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:451
msgid ""
"The file has to be saved in any of the following formats: TIF, TGA, PNG, "
"BMP, JPG, NOL, RGB and SGI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:453
msgid ""
"Save the texture file in the folder ``Projectroot\\library\\textures``  "
"(see  :ref:`Setting up Projects <setting_up_projects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:459
msgid "Custom Textures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:460
msgid ""
"Custom Textures can be used both for drawing lines and filling areas. "
"Using Custom Textures allows to set many parameters such as: Use As "
"Pattern, using the brightness of the loaded image to modulate the "
"brightness of the Color index to which it is applied; choose the position"
" between Fixed (the texture will be fixed and slide into the character), "
"Automatic (the texture will follow the character position during the "
"animation) and Random (the texture position change at each frame in a "
"random way); Scale, Rotation, apply an Horizontal or Vertical offset and "
"change the Contrast. The Custom Texture will be saved into the Palette "
"and its icon will be replaced with an icon of the loaded texture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:462
msgid "**To add a Custom Texture:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:464
msgid "Select a style in the palette editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:466
msgid ""
"Go in the Texture tab of the Style Editor and press the Custom Texture "
"button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:468
msgid ""
"Go in the Settings tab, use the Load From File field and choose the image"
" (or the image sequence) you want to use as texture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:470
msgid "Press the Preview button to visualize the texture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:476
msgid "Generated Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:478
msgid "|style_editor_generated|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:480
msgid ""
"Generated styles use a number of mathematical functions to create effects"
" that can be used either for vector strokes or for filling areas defined "
"by vectors. They can be selected from a list available in the Generated "
"section of the Vector tab, where styles suitable for vector strokes have "
"a thumbnail representing how they will look as a diagonal line; styles "
"suitable for filling have a thumbnail representing the top right corner "
"piece of an area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:482
msgid ""
"Generated styles can simulate for instance a frieze, a leaf, or a pencil "
"stroke along a vector, or allow you to fill areas with special effects "
"such as polka dots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:484
msgid ""
"Generated styles can be customized by defining the parameters available "
"in the Settings tab. This allows you to have many similar styles, each "
"with a different configuration of settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:486
msgid ""
"Colors used by generated styles can be modified by using the Color tab "
"available in the Style Editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:488
msgid ""
"The first item available in the list allows you to remove the Generated "
"style, in order to return it to a Color style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:490
msgid "**To change colors used by a generated style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:492
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:550
msgid "Move to the Color tab in the Style Editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:494
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:552
msgid "Edit the color using the wheel and sliders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:496
msgid ""
"If the generated style uses more than one color, select the color to edit"
" in the row of swatches available below the Auto and Apply buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:502
msgid "Trail Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:504
msgid "|style_editor_trail|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:506
msgid ""
"Trail styles are available for vector levels only. A trail style repeats "
"an image or an animation level, created with OpenToonz or third party "
"software, along the vectors of a vector level. Trail styles cannot be "
"used to paint areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:508
msgid ""
"In the Trail section on the Vector tab you can select the image or the "
"animation level you want to use as a style. You can add to the list your "
"own animation levels as well: both OpenToonz animation levels (PLI) and "
"full-color images or sequences of full-color images (BMP, JPG, NOL, PIC, "
"PICT, PCT, PNG, RGB, SGI, TGA, TIF and TIFF) are supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:510
#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:534
msgid ""
"PLI levels are rendered according to the vector length and thickness, "
"thus appearing jagged when zoomed in. If the output format is a vector "
"one, then the PLI level will remain vector-based. (see  :ref:`Choosing "
"the Output Settings <choosing_the_output_settings>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:512
msgid ""
"The images are repeated changing their placement and size according to "
"the vector’s shape and thickness. If the animation levels contains "
"different drawings, they are repeated cyclically along the vector length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:514
msgid ""
"Parameters such as the distance between subsequent images along the "
"vector and their rotation can be defined in the Settings tab (see  "
":ref:`Settings <settings>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:516
msgid "**To add a new custom style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:518
msgid ""
"Create an image or an animation level with OpenToonz, or with third-party"
" software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:520
msgid ""
"Save it in the folder ``Projectroot\\library\\custom styles`` (see  "
":ref:`Setting up Projects <setting_up_projects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:526
msgid "Vector Brush Styles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:528
msgid "|style_editor_vectorbrush|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:530
msgid ""
"Vector brush styles are available for vector levels only. A vector brush "
"applies a vector image, created with OpenToonz, along the vector strokes "
"of a vector level. Vector brush styles cannot be used to paint areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:532
msgid ""
"In the Vector Brush section of the Vector tab, you can select the image "
"you want to use as a style. You can add to the list your own PLI images "
"as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:536
msgid ""
"The Vector Brush image is applyed to each stroke of the drawing that use "
"this style according to the stroke’s shape and thickness. If the "
"animation levels used as vector Brush contains different drawings, only "
"the first one will be taken into account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:538
msgid ""
"Colors used by vector brushes can be modified by using the Color tab "
"available in the style editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:540
msgid ""
"The first item available in the list allows you to remove the Vector "
"Brush in order to return it to a Color style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:542
msgid "**To add a new vector brush:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:544
msgid "Create a PLI level with OpenToonz."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:546
msgid ""
"Save it in the folder ``Projectroot\\library\\vector brushes`` (see  "
":ref:`Setting up Projects <setting_up_projects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:548
msgid "**To change colors used by a vector brush style:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:554
msgid ""
"If the vector brush uses more than one color, select the color to edit in"
" the row of swatches available below the Auto and Apply buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:560
msgid "Raster Brushes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:562
msgid "|style_editor_raster|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:564
msgid ""
"Raster brushes are available to paint in raster levels and, with some "
"limitations, in Toonz raster levels. They are essentially brushes "
"compatible with the `MyPaint <http://mypaint.org/about/>`_ open source "
"painting software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:566
msgid ""
"The Raster brushes use the color from the current style as a base, and "
"all its remaining options can be found in the Settings tab of the Style "
"Editor pane (see  :ref:`Settings <settings>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:568
msgid ""
"In Toonz raster levels, currently only additive Raster brushes can be "
"used (i.e. brushes that add paint to a level, not the ones that erase, "
"blend or blur already painted strokes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:570
msgid ""
"In Toonz raster levels, Raster brushes use only the alpha channel "
"(opacity) values of the selected brush to paint with the current style "
"Color, and cannot use any of the other color related settings of that "
"brush."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:572
msgid "In Toonz raster levels, Raster brushes paint only Lines (not Areas)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:579
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:581
msgid "|style_editor_settings|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:583
msgid "The Settings tab is available for defining some color properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:585
msgid ""
"For Toonz raster levels, it contains only the Autopaint for Lines option,"
" that can be used to automatically paint border lines of an area, with "
"the same color used to fill that area (see  :ref:`Using the Autopaint for"
" Lines Option <using_the_autopaint_for_lines_option>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:587
msgid ""
"For Toonz vector levels, it contains parameters only when the style is a "
"generated or trail one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:589
msgid ""
"When the style is a generated one, the Settings tab contains one or more "
"sliders that allow you to finetune the predefined style to your needs. "
"When the style is a trail one, the Settings tab contains two sliders: the"
" Distance sets the space between two subsequent images of the animation "
"level used as a trail; the Rotation sets the angle of all the images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:591
msgid ""
"You can add the same generated or trail style as many times as you want, "
"each time defining different settings for it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:597
msgid "Changing the Type of Style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:598
msgid ""
"When you select color, texture, generated, trail or vector brush in the "
"style editor, you automatically assign it to the current style, thus "
"changing the type of style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:600
msgid ""
"The only exception is when you want to change from a generated or a "
"vector brush style to a color one, because when the current style is a "
"generated or a vector brush one, the Color tab is used for setting its "
"colors. In this case you have first to remove the generated or vector "
"brush style by using the first swatch available in the swatch list, and "
"then move to the Color tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:602
msgid ""
"Note that when you change from a style suitable for both lines and areas "
"to a style suitable only for lines, areas painted with that style will "
"become invisible, and vice versa. For example if you change a style from "
"color to trail, all areas painted with that color will become invisible. "
"If you modify the style so that it is suitable again for lines and areas,"
" the invisible parts will become visible again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:604
msgid "**To change the type of style from color to any other:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:606
msgid "Choose an item in the texture or vector tabs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/managing_palettes_and_styles.rst:608
